      <refsect1 xml:id="desc_nntp_auth_get">
        <title>Description
</title>
        <para>The 
<function>nntp_auth_get()
</function>

   is used to retrieve messages from a 
server requiring authorization.  See nntp_get for more information.
</para>
      </refsect1>
      <refsect1 xml:id="params_nntp_auth_get">
        <title>Parameters
</title>
        <refsect2>
          <title>server
</title>
          <para>The host to connect with. IP address or hostname:port.  There is no default for 
      port, so to connect to the standard port for NNTP, use &lt;hostname/IP address&gt;:119
</para>
        </refsect2>
        <refsect2>
          <title>user
</title>
          <para>The username.
      </para>
        </refsect2>
        <refsect2>
          <title>password</title>
          <para>The user password.

</para>
        </refsect2>
        <refsect2>
          <title>command
</title>
          <para>Command 
<type>string
</type>

  .  Valid values are:
</para>
          <simplelist type="vert">
            <member>article
</member>
            <member>body
</member>
            <member>head
</member>
            <member>stat
</member>
            <member>list
</member>
            <member>group
</member>
            <member>xover
</member>
          </simplelist>
        </refsect2>
        <refsect2>
          <title>group
</title>
          <para>A 
<type>string
</type>

   containing name of the news group.
</para>
        </refsect2>
      </refsect1>
      <refsect1 xml:id="ret_02">
        <title>Return Types
</title>
        <para>A vector of vectors the content depends of command.
</para>
      </refsect1>
